  21. (* Reloading for the AMD64 *)

  23. (* Summary of instruction set constraints:
  24.    "S" means either stack or register, "R" means register only.
  25.    Operation                    Res     Arg1    Arg2
  26.      Imove                      R       S
  27.                              or S       R
  28.      Iconst_int                 S if 32-bit signed, R otherwise
  29.      Iconst_float               R
  30.      Iconst_symbol (not PIC)    S
  31.      Iconst_symbol (PIC)        R
  32.      Icall_ind                          R
  33.      Itailcall_ind                      R
  34.      Iload                      R       R       R
  35.      Istore                             R       R
  36.      Iintop(Icomp)              R       R       S
  37.                             or  R       S       R
  38.      Iintop(Imul|Idiv|Imod)     R       R       S
  39.      Iintop(Imulh)              R       R       S
  40.      Iintop(shift)              S       S       R
  41.      Iintop(others)             R       R       S
  42.                             or  S       S       R
  43.      Iintop_imm(Iadd, n)/lea    R       R
  44.      Iintop_imm(Imul, n)        R       R
  45.      Iintop_imm(Icomp, n)       R       S
  46.      Iintop_imm(others)         S       S
  47.      Inegf...Idivf              R       R       S
  48.      Ifloatofint                R       S
  49.      Iintoffloat                R       S
  50.      Ispecific(Ilea)            R       R       R
  51.      Ispecific(Ifloatarithmem)  R       R       R

  53.    Conditional branches:
  54.      Iinttest                           S       R

  65. class reload = object (self)

  67. inherit Reloadgen.reload_generic as super

  69. method! reload_operation op arg res =
  70.   match op with
  71.   | Iintop(Iadd|Isub|Iand|Ior|Ixor|Icheckbound) ->
  72.       (* One of the two arguments can reside in the stack, but not both *)
  73.       if stackp arg.(0) && stackp arg.(1)
  74.       then ([|arg.(0); self#makereg arg.(1)|], res)
  75.       else (arg, res)
  76.   | Iintop(Icomp _) ->
  77.       (* The result must be a register (PR#11803) *)
  78. ‌      let res = self#makeregs res in
  79.       (* One of the two arguments can reside in the stack, but not both *)
  80.       if stackp arg.(0) && stackp arg.(1)
  81.       then ([|arg.(0); self#makereg arg.(1)|], res)
  82.       else (arg, res)
  83.   | Iintop_imm(Iadd, _) when arg.(0).loc <> res.(0).loc ->
  84.       (* This add will be turned into a lea; args and results must be
  85.          in registers *)
  86.       super#reload_operation op arg res
  87.   | Iintop_imm(Imul, _) ->
  88.       (* The result (= the argument) must be a register (#10626) *)
  89.       if stackp arg.(0)
  90. ‌      then (let r = self#makereg arg.(0) in ([|r|], [|r|]))
  91.       else (arg, res)
  92.   | Iintop_imm(Icomp _, _) ->
  93.       (* The result must be in a register (PR#11803) *)
  94.       (arg, self#makeregs res)
  95.   | Iintop(Imulh | Idiv | Imod | Ilsl | Ilsr | Iasr)
  96.   | Iintop_imm(_, _) ->
  97.       (* The argument(s) and results can be either in register or on stack *)
  98.       (* Note: Imulh, Idiv, Imod: arg(0) and res(0) already forced in regs
  99.                Ilsl, Ilsr, Iasr: arg(1) already forced in regs *)
  100.       (arg, res)
  101.   | Iintop(Imul) | Iaddf | Isubf | Imulf | Idivf ->
  102.       (* First argument (= result) must be in register, second arg
  103.          can reside in the stack *)
  104.       if stackp arg.(0)
  105. ‌      then (let r = self#makereg arg.(0) in ([|r; arg.(1)|], [|r|]))
  106.       else (arg, res)
  107.   | Ifloatofint | Iintoffloat ->
  108.       (* Result must be in register, but argument can be on stack *)
  109.       (arg, (if stackp res.(0) then [| self#makereg res.(0) |] else res))
  110.   | Iconst_int n ->
  111.       if n <= 0x7FFFFFFFn && n >= -0x80000000n
  112.       then (arg, res)
  113.       else super#reload_operation op arg res
  114.   | Iconst_symbol _ ->
  115.       if !Clflags.pic_code || !Clflags.dlcode || Arch.win64
  116.       then super#reload_operation op arg res
  117.       else (arg, res)
  118.   | _ -> (* Other operations: all args and results in registers *)
  119.       super#reload_operation op arg res

  121. method! reload_test tst arg =
  122.   match tst with
  123.     Iinttest _ ->
  124.       (* One of the two arguments can reside on stack *)
  125.       if stackp arg.(0) && stackp arg.(1)
  126.       then [| self#makereg arg.(0); arg.(1) |]
  127.       else arg
  128.   | Ifloattest (CFlt | CFnlt | CFle | CFnle) ->
  129.       (* Cf. emit.mlp: we swap arguments in this case *)
  130.       (* First argument can be on stack, second must be in register *)
  131.       if stackp arg.(1)
  132.       then [| arg.(0); self#makereg arg.(1) |]
  133.       else arg
  134.   | Ifloattest (CFeq | CFneq | CFgt | CFngt | CFge | CFnge) ->
  135.       (* Second argument can be on stack, first must be in register *)
  136.       if stackp arg.(0)
  137.       then [| self#makereg arg.(0); arg.(1) |]
  138.       else arg
  139.   | _ ->
  140.       (* The argument(s) can be either in register or on stack *)
  141.       arg

  143. end
